wwwMIB.description: This WWW service MIB module is applicable to services realized by a family of 'Document Transfer Protocols' (DTP). Examples of DTPs are HTTP and FTP.

WwwRequestType.name: WwwRequestType
WwwRequestType.description: The WwwRequestType defines the textual identification of request types used by a document transfer protocol. For the proper values for a given DTP, refer to the protocol mappings for that DTP.

WwwResponseType.name: WwwResponseType
WwwResponseType.description: The WwwResponseType defines the different response values used by document transfer protocols. For the proper values for a given DTP, refer to the protocol mappings for that DTP.

WwwOperStatus.name: WwwOperStatus
WwwOperStatus.description: The operational status of a WWW service. 'down' indicates that the service is not available. 'running' indicates that the service is operational and available. 'halted' indicates that the service is operational but not available. 'congested' indicates that the service is operational but no additional inbound associations can be accommodated. 'restarting' indicates that the service is currently unavailable but is in the process of restarting and will be available soon.

WwwDocName.name: WwwDocName
WwwDocName.description: The server relative name of a document. If the URL were http://www.x.org/standards/search/search.cgi?string=test then the value of this textual convention would resolve to '/standards/search/search.cgi'. This textual convention uses the character set for URIs as defined in RFC 2396 section 2.

wwwServiceTable.name: wwwServiceTable
wwwServiceTable.description: The table of the WWW services known by the SNMP agent.

wwwServiceEntry.name: wwwServiceEntry
wwwServiceEntry.description: Details about a particular WWW service.

wwwServiceIndex.name: wwwServiceIndex
wwwServiceIndex.description: An integer used to uniquely identify a WWW service. The value must be the same as the corresponding value of the applSrvIndex defined in the Application Management MIB (APPLICATION-MIB) if the applSrvIndex object is available. It might be necessary to manually configure sub-agents in order to meet this requirement.

wwwServiceDescription.name: wwwServiceDescription
wwwServiceDescription.description: Textual description of the WWW service. This shall include at least the vendor and version number of the application realizing the WWW service. In a minimal case, this might be the Product Token (see RFC 2068) for the application.

wwwServiceContact.name: wwwServiceContact
wwwServiceContact.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this service, together with information on how to contact this person. For instance, this might be a string containing an email address, e.g. '<webmaster@domain.name>'.

wwwServiceProtocol.name: wwwServiceProtocol
wwwServiceProtocol.reference: The OID values applTCPProtoID and applUDPProtoID are defined in the NETWORK-SERVICES-MIB (RFC 2248).
wwwServiceProtocol.description: An identification of the primary protocol in use by this service. For Internet applications, the IANA maintains a registry of the OIDs which correspond to well-known application protocols. If the application protocol is not listed in the registry, an OID value of the form {applTCPProtoID port} or {applUDPProtoID port} are used for TCP-based and UDP-based protocols, respectively. In either case 'port' corresponds to the primary port number being used by the protocol.

wwwServiceName.name: wwwServiceName
wwwServiceName.description: The fully qualified domain name by which this service is known. This object must contain the virtual host name if the service is realized for a virtual host.

wwwServiceType.name: wwwServiceType
wwwServiceType.description: The application type using or realizing this WWW service.

wwwServiceStartTime.name: wwwServiceStartTime
wwwServiceStartTime.description: The date and time when this WWW service was last started. The value SHALL be '0000000000000000'H if the last start time of this WWW service is not known.

wwwServiceOperStatus.name: wwwServiceOperStatus
wwwServiceOperStatus.description: Indicates the operational status of the WWW service.

wwwServiceLastChange.name: wwwServiceLastChange
wwwServiceLastChange.description: The date and time when this WWW service entered its current operational state. The value SHALL be '0000000000000000'H if the time of the last state change is not known.

wwwSummaryTable.name: wwwSummaryTable
wwwSummaryTable.description: The table providing overview statistics for the WWW services on this system.

wwwSummaryEntry.name: wwwSummaryEntry
wwwSummaryEntry.description: Overview statistics for an individual service.

wwwSummaryInRequests.name: wwwSummaryInRequests
wwwSummaryInRequests.description: The number of requests successfully received.

wwwSummaryInResponses.name: wwwSummaryInResponses
wwwSummaryInResponses.description: The number of responses successfully received.

wwwSummaryInBytes.name: wwwSummaryInBytes
wwwSummaryInBytes.description: The number of content bytes received.

wwwSummaryInLowBytes.name: wwwSummaryInLowBytes
wwwSummaryInLowBytes.description: The lowest thirty-two bits of wwwSummaryInBytes.

wwwSummaryOutBytes.name: wwwSummaryOutBytes
wwwSummaryOutBytes.description: The number of content bytes transmitted.

wwwSummaryOutLowBytes.name: wwwSummaryOutLowBytes
wwwSummaryOutLowBytes.description: The lowest thirty-two bits of wwwSummaryOutBytes.

wwwRequestInTable.name: wwwRequestInTable
wwwRequestInTable.description: The table providing detailed statistics for requests received by WWW services on this system.

wwwRequestInEntry.name: wwwRequestInEntry
wwwRequestInEntry.description: Request statistics for an individual service.

wwwRequestInIndex.name: wwwRequestInIndex
wwwRequestInIndex.description: The particular request type the statistics apply to.

wwwRequestInRequests.name: wwwRequestInRequests
wwwRequestInRequests.description: The number of requests of this type received by this WWW service.

wwwRequestInBytes.name: wwwRequestInBytes
wwwRequestInBytes.description: The number of content bytes per request type received by this WWW service.

wwwRequestInLastTime.name: wwwRequestInLastTime
wwwRequestInLastTime.description: The date and time when the last byte of the last complete request of this type was received by this WWW service. The value SHALL be '0000000000000000'H if no request of this type has been received yet.

wwwRequestOutTable.name: wwwRequestOutTable
wwwRequestOutTable.description: The table providing detailed statistics for requests generated by the services on this system.

wwwRequestOutEntry.name: wwwRequestOutEntry
wwwRequestOutEntry.description: Request statistics for an individual service.

wwwRequestOutIndex.name: wwwRequestOutIndex
wwwRequestOutIndex.description: The particular request type the statistics apply to.

wwwRequestOutRequests.name: wwwRequestOutRequests
wwwRequestOutRequests.description: The number of requests of this type generated by this WWW service.

wwwRequestOutBytes.name: wwwRequestOutBytes
wwwRequestOutBytes.description: The number of content bytes per requests type generated by this WWW service.

wwwRequestOutLastTime.name: wwwRequestOutLastTime
wwwRequestOutLastTime.description: The date and time when the first byte of the last request of this type was send by this WWW service. The value SHALL be '0000000000000000'H if no request of this type has been send yet.

wwwResponseInTable.name: wwwResponseInTable
wwwResponseInTable.description: The table providing detailed statistics for responses received by WWW services on this system.

wwwResponseInEntry.name: wwwResponseInEntry
wwwResponseInEntry.description: Response statistics for an individual service.

wwwResponseInIndex.name: wwwResponseInIndex
wwwResponseInIndex.description: The particular response type the statistics apply to.

wwwResponseInResponses.name: wwwResponseInResponses
wwwResponseInResponses.description: The number of responses of this type received by this WWW service.

wwwResponseInBytes.name: wwwResponseInBytes
wwwResponseInBytes.description: The number of content bytes per response type received by this WWW service.

wwwResponseInLastTime.name: wwwResponseInLastTime
wwwResponseInLastTime.description: The date and time when the last byte of the last complete response of this type was received by this WWW service. The value SHALL be '0000000000000000'H if no response of this type has been received yet.

wwwResponseOutTable.name: wwwResponseOutTable
wwwResponseOutTable.description: The table providing detailed statistics for responses generated by services on this system.

wwwResponseOutEntry.name: wwwResponseOutEntry
wwwResponseOutEntry.description: Response statistics for an individual service.

wwwResponseOutIndex.name: wwwResponseOutIndex
wwwResponseOutIndex.description: The particular response type the statistics apply to.

wwwResponseOutResponses.name: wwwResponseOutResponses
wwwResponseOutResponses.description: The number of responses of this type generated by this WWW service.

wwwResponseOutBytes.name: wwwResponseOutBytes
wwwResponseOutBytes.description: The number of content bytes per response type generated by this WWW service.

wwwResponseOutLastTime.name: wwwResponseOutLastTime
wwwResponseOutLastTime.description: The date and time when the first byte of the last response of this type was sent by this WWW service. The value SHALL be '0000000000000000'H if response of this type has been send yet.

wwwDocCtrlTable.name: wwwDocCtrlTable
wwwDocCtrlTable.description: A table which controls how the MIB implementation collects and maintains document statistics.

wwwDocCtrlEntry.name: wwwDocCtrlEntry
wwwDocCtrlEntry.description: An entry used to configure the wwwDocLastNTable, the wwwDocBucketTable, the wwwDocAccessTopNTable, and the wwwDocBytesTopNTable.

wwwDocCtrlLastNSize.name: wwwDocCtrlLastNSize
wwwDocCtrlLastNSize.description: The maximum number of entries in the wwwDocLastNTable.

wwwDocCtrlLastNLock.name: wwwDocCtrlLastNLock
wwwDocCtrlLastNLock.description: This object allows a manager to lock the wwwDocLastNTable in order to retrieve the wwwDocLastNTable in a consistent state. The agent is expected to take a snapshot of the wwwDocLastNTable when it is locked and to continue updating the real wwwDocLastNTable table so that recent information is available as soon as the wwwDocLastNTable is unlocked again. Setting this object to a value greater than 0 will lock the table. The timer ticks backwards until it reaches 0. The table unlocks automatically once the timer reaches 0 and the timer stops ticking. A manager can increase the timer to request more time to read the table. However, any attempt to decrease the timer will fail with an inconsistentValue error. This rule ensures that multiple managers can simultaneously lock and retrieve the wwwDocLastNTable. Note that managers must cooperate in using wwwDocCtrlLastNLock. In particular, a manager MUST not keep the wwwDocLastNTable locked when it is not necessary to finish a retrieval operation.

wwwDocCtrlBuckets.name: wwwDocCtrlBuckets
wwwDocCtrlBuckets.description: The maximum number of buckets maintained by the agent before the oldest bucket is deleted. The buckets are used to populate the wwwDocAccessTopNTable and the wwwDocBytesTopNTable. The time interval captured in each bucket can be configured by setting the wwwDocCtrlBucketTimeInterval object.

wwwDocCtrlBucketTimeInterval.name: wwwDocCtrlBucketTimeInterval
wwwDocCtrlBucketTimeInterval.description: The time interval after which a new bucket is created. Changing this object has no effect on existing buckets.

wwwDocCtrlTopNSize.name: wwwDocCtrlTopNSize
wwwDocCtrlTopNSize.description: The maximum number of entries shown in the wwwDocAccessTopNTable and the wwwDocBytesTopNTable. Changing this object has no effect on existing buckets.

wwwDocLastNTable.name: wwwDocLastNTable
wwwDocLastNTable.description: The table which logs the last N access attempts.

wwwDocLastNEntry.name: wwwDocLastNEntry
wwwDocLastNEntry.description: An entry which describes a recent access attempt.

wwwDocLastNIndex.name: wwwDocLastNIndex
wwwDocLastNIndex.description: An arbitrary monotonically increasing integer number used for indexing the wwwDocLastNTable. The first document accessed appears in the table with this index value equal to one. Each subsequent document is indexed with the next sequential index value. The Nth document accessed will be indexed by N. This table presents a sliding window of the last wwwDocCtrlLastNSize documents accessed. Thus, entries in this table will be indexed by N-wwwDocCtrlLastNSize thru N if N > wwwDocCtrlLastNSize and 1 thru N if N <= wwwDocCtrlLastNSize. The wwwDocCtrlLastNLock attribute can be used to lock this table to allow the manager to read its contents.

wwwDocLastNName.name: wwwDocLastNName
wwwDocLastNName.description: The name of the document for which access was attempted.

wwwDocLastNTimeStamp.name: wwwDocLastNTimeStamp
wwwDocLastNTimeStamp.description: The date and time of the last attempt to access this document.

wwwDocLastNRequestType.name: wwwDocLastNRequestType
wwwDocLastNRequestType.description: The protocol request type which was received by the server when this document access was attempted.

wwwDocLastNResponseType.name: wwwDocLastNResponseType
wwwDocLastNResponseType.description: The protocol response type which was sent to the client as a result of this attempt to access a document. This object contains the type of the primary response if there were multiple responses to a single request.

wwwDocLastNStatusMsg.name: wwwDocLastNStatusMsg
wwwDocLastNStatusMsg.description: This object contains a human readable description of the reason why the wwwDocLastNResponseType was returned to the client. This object defines the implementation-specific reason if the value of wwwDocLastNResponseType indicates an error. For example, this object can indicate that the requested document could not be transferred due to a timeout condition or the document could not be transferred because a 'soft link' pointing to the document could not be resolved.

wwwDocLastNBytes.name: wwwDocLastNBytes
wwwDocLastNBytes.description: The number of content bytes that were returned as a result of this attempt to access a document.

wwwDocBucketTable.name: wwwDocBucketTable
wwwDocBucketTable.description: This table provides administrative summary information for the buckets maintained per WWW service.

wwwDocBucketEntry.name: wwwDocBucketEntry
wwwDocBucketEntry.description: An entry which describes the parameters associated with a particular bucket.

wwwDocBucketIndex.name: wwwDocBucketIndex
wwwDocBucketIndex.description: An arbitrary monotonically increasing integer number used for indexing the wwwDocBucketTable. The index number wraps to 1 whenever the maximum value is reached.

wwwDocBucketTimeStamp.name: wwwDocBucketTimeStamp
wwwDocBucketTimeStamp.description: The date and time when the bucket was made available.

wwwDocBucketAccesses.name: wwwDocBucketAccesses
wwwDocBucketAccesses.description: The total number of access attempts for any document provided by this WWW service during the time interval over which this bucket was created.

wwwDocBucketDocuments.name: wwwDocBucketDocuments
wwwDocBucketDocuments.description: The total number of different documents for which access was attempted this this WWW service during the time interval over which this bucket was created.

wwwDocBucketBytes.name: wwwDocBucketBytes
wwwDocBucketBytes.description: The total number of content bytes which were transferred from this WWW service during the time interval over which this bucket was created.

wwwDocAccessTopNTable.name: wwwDocAccessTopNTable
wwwDocAccessTopNTable.description: The table of the most frequently accessed documents in a given bucket. This table is sorted by the column wwwDocAccessTopNAccesses. Entries having the same number of accesses are secondarily sorted by wwwDocAccessTopNBytes. Entries with the same number of accesses and the same number of bytes will have an arbitrary order.

wwwDocAccessTopNEntry.name: wwwDocAccessTopNEntry
wwwDocAccessTopNEntry.description: An entry in the top N table sorted by document accesses.

wwwDocAccessTopNIndex.name: wwwDocAccessTopNIndex
wwwDocAccessTopNIndex.description: An arbitrary monotonically increasing integer number used for indexing the wwwDocAccessTopNTable. The index is inversely correlated to the sorting order of the table. The document with the highest access count will get the index value 1.

wwwDocAccessTopNName.name: wwwDocAccessTopNName
wwwDocAccessTopNName.description: The name of the document for which access was attempted.

wwwDocAccessTopNAccesses.name: wwwDocAccessTopNAccesses
wwwDocAccessTopNAccesses.description: The total number of access attempts for this document.

wwwDocAccessTopNBytes.name: wwwDocAccessTopNBytes
wwwDocAccessTopNBytes.description: The total number of content bytes that were transmitted as a result of attempts to access this document.

wwwDocAccessTopNLastResponseType.name: wwwDocAccessTopNLastResponseType
wwwDocAccessTopNLastResponseType.description: The protocol response type which was sent to the client as a result of the last attempt to access this document. This object contains the type of the primary response if there were multiple responses to a single request.

wwwDocBytesTopNTable.name: wwwDocBytesTopNTable
wwwDocBytesTopNTable.description: The table of the documents which caused most network traffic in a given bucket. This table is sorted by the column wwwDocBytesTopNBytes. Entries having the same number bytes are secondarily sorted by wwwDocBytesTopNAccesses. Entries with the same number of accesses and the same number of bytes will have an arbitrary order.

wwwDocBytesTopNEntry.name: wwwDocBytesTopNEntry
wwwDocBytesTopNEntry.description: An entry in the top N table sorted by network traffic.

wwwDocBytesTopNIndex.name: wwwDocBytesTopNIndex
wwwDocBytesTopNIndex.description: An arbitrary monotonically increasing integer number used for indexing the wwwDocBytesTopNTable. The index is inversely correlated to the sorting order of the table. The document with the highest byte count will get the index value 1.

wwwDocBytesTopNName.name: wwwDocBytesTopNName
wwwDocBytesTopNName.description: The name of the document for which access was attempted.

wwwDocBytesTopNAccesses.name: wwwDocBytesTopNAccesses
wwwDocBytesTopNAccesses.description: The total number of access attempts for this document.

wwwDocBytesTopNBytes.name: wwwDocBytesTopNBytes
wwwDocBytesTopNBytes.description: The total number of content bytes that were transmitted as a result of attempts to access this document.

wwwDocBytesTopNLastResponseType.name: wwwDocBytesTopNLastResponseType
wwwDocBytesTopNLastResponseType.description: The protocol response type which was sent to the client as a result of the last attempt to access this document. This object contains the type of the primary response if there were multiple responses to a single request.

wwwMinimalCompliance.name: wwwMinimalCompliance
wwwMinimalCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP agents which implement the minimal subset of the WWW-MIB. Implementors might choose this subset for high-performance server where full compliance might be to expensive.

wwwFullCompliance.name: wwwFullCompliance
wwwFullCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP agents which implement the full WWW-MIB.

wwwServiceGroup.name: wwwServiceGroup
wwwServiceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the WWW services known by the SNMP agent.

wwwSummaryGroup.name: wwwSummaryGroup
wwwSummaryGroup.description: A collection of objects providing summary statistics about requests and responses generated and received by a WWW service.

wwwRequestInGroup.name: wwwRequestInGroup
wwwRequestInGroup.description: A collection of objects providing detailed statistics about requests received by a WWW service.

wwwRequestOutGroup.name: wwwRequestOutGroup
wwwRequestOutGroup.description: A collection of objects providing detailed statistics about requests generated by a WWW service.

wwwResponseInGroup.name: wwwResponseInGroup
wwwResponseInGroup.description: A collection of objects providing detailed statistics about responses received by a WWW service.

wwwResponseOutGroup.name: wwwResponseOutGroup
wwwResponseOutGroup.description: A collection of objects providing detailed statistics about responses generated by a WWW service.

wwwDocumentGroup.name: wwwDocumentGroup
wwwDocumentGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about accesses to documents.
